&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Clinical Pharmacist – Bank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Papworth Hospital is looking for Clinical Pharmacists to join us on a flexible basis to support our ward-based clinical pharmacy teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for clinical pharmacists with experience of working in the hospital environment to help us provide patient-focused pharmaceutical care on our cardiology, cardiac surgery, and thoracic medicine wards. The successful candidate would be expected to work as part of a team of pharmacists and pharmacy technicians to provide a clinical pharmacy service to a group of wards. Typical roles include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medicines reconciliation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review of inpatient prescriptions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribution to multidisciplinary ward rounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitation of discharge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates should have at least 12 months post-registration experience in a hospital environment and have completed or be undertaking a post-graduate qualification in pharmacy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pharmacy department at Royal Papworth is a small, friendly team working in a new, purpose-built hospital. We are a digitally enabled department, with electronic prescribing in place in all areas and a robot to support a safe and timely dispensing process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a clinical pharmacist who is keen to join our friendly team on a flexible basis, then we very much look forward to discussing opportunities with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any further information please contact: Christopher McCorquodale (Deputy Chief Pharmacist) christopher.mccorquodale@nhs.net or 01223 638179.&lt;/p&gt;
